[[!meta title="Energy Drink — NOS Grand Prix Guava"]]
[[!tag Energy_Drink Review]]

NOS. I thought you were dead, I thought you were gone!

<table class="no-border">
<tr><td class="no-border">[[!template id="userbox-nos.tmpl"]]</td></tr>
</table>

As a subsidiary of Monster I thought they'd give you the axe, considering Moster
has so many sugary flavors already. I was wrong. Happily wrong.

NOS Grand Prix Guava released in April 2026 and displaced [[NOS_Sonic_Sour]].
Their lineup is now 4-wide: [[NOS]], [[NOS_Zero_Sugar]], [[NOS_GT_Grape]] and
this one, Grand Prix Guava.

<figure>
[[!template id="hooya-img.tmpl" cid="bafkreiao54h2ahapdook3ljnhcp2z6pptkh5xtg3b7o7iopkqgxm3lf7nq" size=medium]]
</figure>

Grand Prix Guava smells and tastes like candy, like bubblegum in particular.
Real bubblegum. That one bubblegum with the punk rock duck on it that looks like
Lil Uzi Vert.

<figure>
[[!template id="hooya-img.tmpl" cid="bafkreihghv4lwdasynzr7pjerd7us3i7ymj2kfwbpx2wkrfgm65dsgfpxu" size=small]]
</figure>

I'm pretty sure they still sell it in that wrapper. Anyway, with 200mg of
caffeine as opposed to NOS' typical 160mg the duck captures how I feel after
downing this one. Plus the colorway almost matches.

Of course the NOS is sugary. They all are except [[NOS_Zero_Sugar]]. But that
doesn't matter. I can always budget a NOS into my daily routine, especially one
that is as good as this one.

| | Amount |
| --- | --- |
| Volume | 16 floz |
| Calories | 210cal |
| Caffeine | 200mg |

